Assuming that the count <italic>y</italic><sub><italic>gi</italic></sub> follows a Poisson distribution for repeated sequencing runs of the same RNA sample, a well known formula for the variance of a mixture distribution implies:
<disp-formula><graphic xlink:href="gks042u2"/></disp-formula>
Dividing both sides by <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="gks042i3.jpg"/></inline-formula> gives
